    <docsection name="doc_1"
        text="Description">
        <doctext name="txt"
            text="SiFive FU540-C000 SoC module."/>
        <doctext name="txt_1"
            text="On start up or reset, the reset code at 0x1004 will jump to a jump table entry indexed by the MSEL register at address 0x1000 (default initial MSEL value is 0xf which will cause a jump to address 0x10000). Use the msel peripheral&apos;s MSEL parameter to change the initial value of this register."/>
        <doctext name="txt_2"
            text="To run a bare metal application use the --program command line option to specify an elf file to be loaded. It must be linked to use addresses corresponding to the implemented memory regions. The --program option will override the initial pc with the ELF file&apos;s start address."/>
        <doctext name="txt_3"
            text="To facilitate booting Linux an OVP SmartLoader psuedo-peripheral has been included that provides the functionality of the ZSBL/FSBL. The SmartLoader&apos;s dtb parameter should be used to specify the device tree blob file to load, and the bbl elf file should be loaded using the --objfilenoentry command line option."/>
    </docsection>
    <docsection name="doc_2"
        text="Reference">
        <doctext name="txt"
            text="SiFive Freedom U540-C000 Manual FU540-C000-v1.0.pdf (https://www.sifive.com/documentation/chips/freedom-u540-c000-manual)"/>
    </docsection>
    <docsection name="doc_3"
        text="Limitations">
        <doctext name="txt"
            text="Caches and the Cache Controller are not modeled."/>
        <doctext name="txt_1"
            text="The Instruction Tightly Integrated Memory (ITIM) is implemented simply as RAM. Deallocation by writing to the byte immediately following the memory is a NOP."/>
        <doctext name="txt_2"
            text="The L2 Loosely Integrated Memory (L2-LIM) is implemented simply as RAM. It is always available, since the Cache Controller is not modeled."/>
        <doctext name="txt_3"
            text="The L2 Scratchpad memory is not modeled."/>
        <doctext name="txt_4"
            text="The Platform DMA Engine (PDMA) is not modeled."/>
        <doctext name="txt_5"
            text="The Pulse Width Modulator (PWM) is not modeled."/>
        <doctext name="txt_6"
            text="The Inter-Integrated Circuit (I2C) Master Interface is not modeled."/>
        <doctext name="txt_7"
            text="The Serial Peripheral Interfaces (SPI) are not modeled. Instead a Virtio Block MMIO device has been added at reserved address 0x1f000000, using interrupt 54."/>
        <doctext name="txt_8"
            text="The General Purpose Input/Output Controller (GPIO) is modeled with register stubs only."/>
        <doctext name="txt_9"
            text="The One-Time Programmable Memory Interface (OTP) is not modeled."/>
        <doctext name="txt_10"
            text="DDR controller is modeled with register stubs only. DDR memory is modeled as RAM."/>
        <doctext name="txt_11"
            text="The Debug Interface is not modeled."/>
    </docsection>
